  "prompt": "Who are the best angel investors of all time?",
  "response": "Identifying the \"best\" angel investors of all time can be somewhat subjective as it depends on various factors such as successful investments, returns, influence, and contributions to the startup ecosystem. However, a few angel investors have gained significant attention and recognition for their outstanding achievements:\n\n1. **Ron Conway**: Often called \"The Godfather of Silicon Valley,\" Ron Conway is known for his prolific investments in early-stage startups. His portfolio includes companies like Google, Facebook, Zappos, and Airbnb.\n\n2. **Chris Sacca**: Formerly running Lowercase Capital, Chris Sacca is recognized for his early investments in Twitter, Uber, Instagram, and Stripe. He has a reputation for identifying potential in companies that later become industry giants.\n\n3. **Naval Ravikant**: Co-founder of AngelList, Naval Ravikant has invested in numerous successful startups, including Twitter, Uber, Yammer, and Postmates. He is known for his insightful commentary on startups and investing.\n\n4. **Paul Buchheit**: Creator of Gmail and a partner at Y Combinator, Paul Buchheit has invested in many high-profile companies such as Dropbox, Airbnb, and Stripe. His technical expertise and visionary approach make him a respected figure in angel investing circles.\n\n5. **Mitch Kapor**: Founder of Lotus 1-2-3 and co-founder of Mozilla Foundation, Mitch Kapor has invested in various companies like Uber, Twilio, and SurveyMonkey. He is also known for his focus on social impact and diversity in tech.\n\n6. **Jeff Bezos**: While he's primarily known as the founder of Amazon, Jeff Bezos has made several notable angel investments through his personal venture capital firm, Bezos Expeditions. His investments include companies like Airbnb and Uber.\n\nThese investors are celebrated not only for their financial success but also for their contributions to building the startup ecosystem and guiding many companies to monumental success.",
